Visual Studio Code for Web enables editing and publishing of web pages on your website.
For a command line interface and more advanced capabilities, install the Power Platform Extension for VS Code, available in the VS Code Marketplace for desktop.

Your files are stored in nested folders under your site name.
The individual page files can be found in the web-pages folder under your site name.
All of your pages are arranged into HTML, CSS and JS files inside the folder with the respective page name.
To learn more about the Power Pages file system in VS Code for Web, visit our [documentation](command:powerplatform-walkthrough.fileSystem-documentation). [Open site folder](command:powerplatform-walkthrough.fileSystem-open-folder)
